  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: vend-utilities (npm)",
  "details": "Vend-utilities@14.12.11 executes a host reconnaissance beacon at install time. The preinstall hook runs index.js, which collects system information (hostname, platform, architecture, home directory, username, uid/gid/shell, OS type/release, memory, CPU count, whoami output, id output, current working directory) and exfiltrates it via an HTTPS POST to the C2 endpoint 6cjy9tle5weq8pr6m8r5znzd349vxmlb[.]oastify[.]com/detox56. The package also ships a large Instagram username list as filler (file 'i'), unrelated to the malicious payload.",
